    {
      "title": "The Hundred (المائة)",
      "titleArabic": "الْمِائَةُ",
      "content": [
        "مِائَة (one hundred) is مُفْرَدَة مُؤَنَّثَة (singular feminine). It can be written مِائَة or مِئَة. The counted noun after it is مُفْرَد مَجْرُور (singular genitive) - added to it in إِضَافَة.",
        "مِائَة طَالِبٍ (100 students - male), مِائَة طَالِبَةٍ (100 students - female). The gender of مِائَة doesn't change - it's always feminine. Only the counted noun changes."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "مِائَة: singular feminine",
        "Counted noun: singular genitive",
        "إِضَافَة structure",
        "Gender of مِائَة doesn't change"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مِائَةُ رَجُلٍ", "english": "One hundred men" },
        { "arabic": "مِائَةُ امْرَأَةٍ", "english": "One hundred women" },
        { "arabic": "مِائَةُ كِتَابٍ", "english": "One hundred books" },
        { "arabic": "مِائَةُ سَنَةٍ", "english": "One hundred years" }
